<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12144f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12144f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12144f"> 144(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">H</font> married, priest</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Potitus et Calpurnius &eacute;taient dans les ordres et ils &eacute;taient mari&eacute;s. Ceci ne peut beaucoup surprendre. Ces deux hommes v&eacute;curent dans une p&eacute;riode de transition, avant que la r&egrave;gle du c&eacute;libat eccl&eacute;siastique ait &eacute;t&eacute; universellement admise. <br><font color="green">[29: The fact that Potitus and Calpurnius were in Holy Orders, and yet were married, need not cause us much surprise. These two men lived in the time of transition, before the rule of ecclesiastical celibacy was universally admitted.]</font> <small> Riguet, Abb&eacute; <a name="RTSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RTSP"><cite title="source">Saint Patrice</cite></a> (1911) 34</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
